{ This method will send an email with multiple MIME body parts of which types are text, html or file. In the current JMail bridge implementation, the protocol used to send email messages is always 'smtp'. It wil use the following attributes of the jmail-interface:
outgoing-email-host user-name password outgoing-email-from-address }
result: text = "Not connected";
begin
if the gsi-interface-status of io = 2 then result = call _jmail-rpc-send-mime-mail(_jmail-gsi-config(io), the outgoing-email-protocol of io, the outgoing-email-host of io, the outgoing-email-host-port of io, the outgoing-email-ssl-enable of io, the user-name of io, the password of io, to-email-addresses, cc-email-addresses, sequence ( ), the outgoing-email-from-address of io, subject, contents) across io;
return result;
end

